				 Sergeants greed fuel for assault 
 A STAFF REPORTER 																								Sergeant Mahan Mukherjee of the wireless squad of Calcutta police on Thursday broke down during interrogation and admitted that he had succumbed to greed when he rounded up a 55-year-old man and robbed him of Rs 20,000 on Tuesday night.																								Mukherjee and his driver, S. Parvat, arrested on Wednesday, were remanded by a city court in police custody till October 15 on charges of robbing Ajit Baran Hazra. The duo were brought to Girish Park police station for interrogation. 																								Late in the evening, the 32-year-old sergeant from Barasat confessed. But the money could not be traced.																								Around 9.30pm on Tuesday, Hazra, a Digha-based businessman, was on his way to see his ailing father at a nursing home in south Calcutta after collecting money from a friend on Beadon Street. 																								As Hazra was crossing Girish Park, his taxi was stopped by Parvat. Hazra was forced into the police jeep, beaten up and robbed by the sergeant.
